column1: #Text=is in the Doab region of Uttar Pradesh , India .
#Text=About 40km away from Agra , it is one of India 's UNESCO World Heritage Sites .
#Text=Literally meaning the city of victory , Fatehpur Sikri was founded by Mughal Emperor Akbar in 1571 and served as the capital from its founding to 1585 .
#Text=Often lumped together with Agra on tourist tours and trails , Fatehpur Sikri is a UNESCO World Heritage Site in its own right .
#Text=While the closest airport is in Agra , the Fatehpur Sikri has its own railway station , a kilometre from the city centre .
#Text=By road and in typical traffic , it is a 50-minute drive from Agra .
#Text=This grand gate was built to commemorate the military triumphs of Mughal emperor Akbar in Gujarat .
#Text=Salim Chishti was a Sufi saint , dearly respected by Emperor Akbar .
#Text=In fact , the emperor held Salim in such great esteem that he named his son Salim ( who would later be known as the Mughal emperor Jahangir ) in honour of the saint .
#Text=The mausoleum built for Salim Chishti in 1580 and 1581 is considered to be one of the greatest examples of Mughal architecture .
#Text=The red sandstone architectural symmetry of the walls and bridges that crisscross the artificial lake or pool is beautiful but the water nowadays is polluted and dirty .
#Text=The funny name of the palace ( samosa referring to the pyramidal shaped dumplings in Indian cuisine ) is because the it does , in fact , resemble a samosa !
#Text=It is clean and well maintained though be wary of the guides in the palace , who can be pushy and touty .
#Text=A high , circular tower covered in spikes that look like elephant tusks .
#Text=Akbar is said to have built it in remembrance of his beloved elephant , Hiran .
#Text=Birbal was a Hindu courtier of Akbar , who ended up becoming one of Akbar 's closest and most trusted military advisors .
#Text=The stone carvings and interior of the palace where Birbal lived are magnificent .
#Text=North Indian vegetarian and vegan food in a casual setting .
#Text=Punjabi and other North Indian food with non-vegetarian and vegetarian options .
#Text=The meals are hearty and feel satisfying after a long day of sightseeing .
